.TH HSH 1 "Simple Shell" "Holberton School"
.SH NAME
hsh \- simple UNIX command interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hsh

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple UNIX command line interpreter.

It reads commands from standard input and executes them using the
execve system call.

The shell works in interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH INVOCATION
Interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ ./hsh
($)
.fi

Non-interactive mode:
.PP
.nf
$ echo "ls" | ./hsh
.fi

.SH BUILTINS
This shell does not implement built-in commands.

.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses the PATH environment variable to locate executables.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell returns the exit status of the last executed command.

.SH AUTHOR
Written by Alexandre GUILLAMON.

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), execve(2), fork(2), wait(2)
